title: John MacArthur says what no-one else will say about the virus (Feels different / Eschatological) - YouTube

author.bio:
Goodbye. https://ruqqus.com/+The_Cabal/post/d9y9/i-told-you-so-all-the

Remember: History repeats, and the unaware are doomed to repeat it.
author.bio_html:
Goodbye. https://ruqqus.com/+The_Cabal/post/d9y9/i-told-you-so-all-the

Remember: History repeats, and the unaware are doomed to repeat it.

body:
Of course it's eschatological, everything is the end of world! The end is nigh, right around the corner, within the next few decades...just as it has been for past 2000 years. I don't blame the initial disciples and apostles for thinking that, because they knew it would be "soon", and their world was REALLY bad back then, but at this point I think we need to realize we don't know when "soon" is. The coronavirus and 2020 are nothing compared to so many other things throughout history, and the world didn't end then either.

I don't trust MacArthur anyway. He's one of those TV preachers who seems mostly motivated by profit and political power.
